HEADWORD: Gambison
<hw>Gam"bi*son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>gambeson</ets>, <ets>gambaison</ets>, fr. <ets>gambais</ets>,
<ets>wambais</ets>, of German origin: cf. MHG. <ets>wambeis</ets>, G.
<ets>wams</ets> doublet, fr. OHG. w<ets>amba</ets>, stomach. See
<er>Womb</er>.]</ety> <def>A defensive garment formerly in use for the
body, made of cloth stuffed and quilted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

